inn1.comm: back of a length on the stumps, tucked off the hip to the gap at square leg
good line outside off, nice carry through to Tim Ambrose
takes a stride towards the bowler, tries to work into the leg side but is taken on the thigh pad
outside off, good judgement from McCullum as he lets it go
good shape from Sidebottom, swings back into McCullum who is taken high on the pads...strangled appeal from Sidebottom
drifts down the leg side, McCullum steps across the stumps but the ball was still wide of leg stump
good finish to the over, McCullum gets a thick inside edge into his pads and down into the off side
excellent start outside off stump, hint of movement off the seam as How is beaten
clipped off the pads through square leg, long leg is very square and keeps them to a single
touch wider outside off, McCullum nearly chases it
testing line from Anderson, McCullum leaves this one alone...a late decision
clipped firmly to short midwicket...Anderson setting a good tone early on
well bowled, fuller outside off and draws McCullum into a drive...the ball scoots past the outside edge.
pushed across outside off stump, How not interested in chasing
hint of swing back from outside off, another leave from How
back of a length on off stump, all defence from How, nothing on offer to hit
comes down the pitch and across his stumps, worked square on the leg side, more intent from How that time
first boundary of the day, albeit leg byes, as Sidebottom drifts onto leg stump and it flies off McCullum's thigh pad down to fine leg...fielder was inside the circle so he had no chance
nearly a breakthrough, McCullum flips this in the air on the leg side but there's no midwicket in place and it falls safely
pushes forward with hard hands, a thick outside edges flies wide of the slips down to third man...Sidebottom is very square and has to slide to prevent a boundary
inswinger from Anderson goes awry down the leg side, big movement in the air but an easy wide
better line from Anderson, full on off stump, more inswing to McCullum and half an appeal as it takes pad first...91mph as well, good pace
this one holds its line outside off, McCullum plays inside the line
squared up on off stump, late movement but the edge from McCullum flies down to third man
another outside edge, this time How turned chest on by the late movement and third man again in action
loses his line down the leg side again, went for another inswinger and it started too straight
corrects himself and goes outside off this time, How lets it go through to Ambrose
keeps McCullum in the crease as he defends firmly into the off side
well bowled, late movement into McCullum who is taken on the pad...big appeal from Sidebottom but Nigel Llong quickly turns it down
nips back again off the seam, McCullum uncomfortable with the extra pace from the surface
super stuff from Sidebottom, makes this one go across McCullum who is beaten on the outside edge as he pushes forward
outside off stump, McCullum goes right across his crease and nudges into the leg side wide of mid-on
hint of width, but How misses out as he goes for a square cut, gets a bottom end back towards the slips
not offering McCullum any width, defended into the leg side
first bouncer of the day, good line over off stump and McCullum ducks
back of a length, defended firmly back towards Anderson
punched wide of mid-off, but again no real timing from McCullum
goes down the leg side again, Anderson has mixed the good with the not-so-good today (what's new some might say)
on off stump, How comes forward with bat and pad together

dropped a huge top edge from How and it loops high behind the batsman, Tim Ambrose back-tracks and eventually gets in position underneath it but drops a clanger...oh dear, not what Kevin Pietersen wanted. Ambrose didn't look confident to start, then seemed to have it under control, however finished having a nightmare
flicked sweetly through square, long leg is quite square so prevents the boundary
outside off and left alone
punched firmly off the front foot up to mid-off, well-taken quick single
nicely bowled, full outside off stump and McCullum goes chasing without really getting to the pitch of the ball
ooh, that looks close as McCullum goes across his stumps again and is taken on the pads...Sidebottom joins the appeal late, replays show it pitched outside leg
good line on off stump, defended with a hop and a skip into the covers
on off stump, defended at the top of the bounce down to mid-on
beaten outside off stump, that was a bit wide to be pushing at
nice shot, a punchy drive down the ground and mid-off (Pietersen) dives over the ball somewhat
turned off the stumps, just to the right of mid-on and another stolen single...England give away a lot of singles to mid-off and mid-on inside the circle
tucked off the hips down to long leg
good line outside off stump, 91mph as well, defended into the covers
once again McCullum moving across the crease, works out through square leg
clipped from outside off stump, through the gap at square leg again
angled into McCullum on leg stump, dropped down by his feet
this one goes across the body outside off stump, McCullum not tempted into chasing anything wide yet
defended firmly square on the off side, can't find the gap
beaten outside off stump, pushing away from his body and Ambrose takes well low down by first slip
hint of width, slashed away hard over the slips and to fine for third man...that's the first boundary off the bat today
straighter this time, flicked firmly out to midwicket
on off stump, defended back down the pitch

almost another opportunity for England, a top edge flies towards deep square-leg and Anderson peddles back from long long, but he is very close to the boundary rope and parries the ball over for six...his momentum would have taken him over even if he had held on

gone this time, a thick outside as How drives and Bopara takes the catch at backward point but, oh boy, that went in with a juggle as well...a heart-stopping moment for Bopara but all ended well for him and England
welcomes Taylor with a bouncer outside off stump, evades with with a duck and a sway
worked between midwicket and mid-on again by McCullum
on middle and off, Taylor defends in his slightly chest-on style...back towards Sidebottom
turned off the stumps out to midwicket
good line on middle, defended down to the off side and Sidebottom hops across in his follow through
steps across in front of off stump, nudges wide of Owais Shah of mid-on for a sharp single
rides some extra bounce, turns it down through short fine-leg who can't stop it with a dive
well bowled, takes the outside edge from off stump and flies along the ground square on the off side
touch wider outside off stump, left alone and too wide for the umpire
tightens his line up, Taylor works out towards midwicket
forced off the back foot into the covers...he has time to play himself in here
defended with soft hands into the off side
cut away hard past gully, it's always a quick outfield at Lord's but Sidebottom makes good ground at third man and keeps them to a single
outside off and McCullum leaves alone...this has been a different type of innings from McCullum so far
takes the pad, but sliding down the leg side and another extra collected towards square leg
forced through the leg side from off stump, still a hint of movement from Anderson, deep square-leg does the fielding
driven to the left of mid-off, rotates the strike again...brings up New Zealand's fifty
short ball outside off stump, McCullum drops his hands and bends his knees
lucky for McCullum, trying to work it through the leg side and gets a thick outside through backward point/wide gully, down to third man...McCullum also loses his footing as he sets off for the run
well bowled, sharp bouncer over off stump and Taylor has to jerk his head inside the line
short and pulled away strongly in front of square, almost straight at the deep fielder
worked from off stump down to short fine-leg, Anderson has a shy but McCullum was well into his ground
beautifully bowled, 89mph, went wide on the crease and beats McCullum's outside edge as he comes right across his stumps...carried through shoulder-height to Ambrose
left alone outside off, more good stuff from Broad
opens the face down to third man
gone! he deserved that, probing line outside off stump and a rather limp push from Taylor sends a regulation edge through to Ambrose
extra bounce from off stump, defended down square on the off side
shapes back into McCullum, kept in defence on off stump and Anderson collects in his follow through
offers a hint of width, slashed very hard through gully and goes one bounce to third man...not far off carrying to the fielder
bit of a lame shot from Styris, a nothing poke outside off and he's lucky not to get the edge
good short ball, outside off and Styris arches his back to sway out of the linbe
excellent finish to the over, beats Styris outside off again
back of a length, nipping back in and pinning him deep, tapped towards backward point and he sets off for a quick single
fuller and wider and he leaves it be
lands on a good length and Styris goes back, driving to cover
short one now, sailing over Styris' left shoulder as he ducks low
short of a length, he gets back and gently taps it wide of point
tucks him up with a well-directed ball but McCullum's at ease, shuffling and nudging off the hips to square leg for a single

gets across and nudges the ball to midwicket and whats this? McCullum's bat has clean broken in half as the ball struck it! I've never seen anything like that ... seriously, ball hit the middle of the bat and the blooming thing just snapped in half, and McCullum ran through for the single with nearly two pieces in his hand ... he has a laugh and calls for a new one ... they don't make 'em like they used to, do they?
moves back in, a touch too straight, and he works a single to leg
short of a length again, off and middle, gets back and taps it back
short one, well dug in, McCullum doesn't play at it and sort of tries to duck but ends up copping it on the arm
better one still, short-pitched and heading into McCullum's shoulder, he gets up and again takes his higher, nearer the shoulder, Anderson working him up
short again but too wide and he uppercuts on the bounce to third man
they're targetting McCullum! Broad this time, dropping in very short and the ball climbs onto him, missing the pull by a fraction as the ball sails past his head, umpire signals one for the over
short of a length, this time he hops back and pushes to cover
short of a length, outside off, and he leaves it be
too straight, nips in and he on-drives to midwicket
half-tracker, forcing Styris down onto his haunches
good slow, getting to the pitch of a fuller one and driving past cover
wrong line, sliding down the pads and he escorts it to fine leg
wide this time, sliding down the pads and no bat on it

edged and taken this time, and thats a massive blow for New Zealand! Much better length from Anderson, forcing McCullum to poke at it and the outside-edge flies into Swann's lap at first slip, well bowled and held
welcomes Flynn by bowling a short one outside leg
terrific length, angling it across Flynn from leg stump and he leaves
streaky way to get off the mark, uppercutting wide of a diving gully
short of a length, gets Stryis back and defending to cover
good length, nipping off the seam and Flynn shoulders arms
fraction shorter but still angling away and Flynn leaves it alone
he's working it across Flynn, marginally wider, and he leaves alone
here comes the expected fuller ball, but its outside leg stump, brushing Flynn's pads as he tries to flick handsomely, and the ball drops before Ambrose
change of pace, fuller outside off stump, dabbed to Pietersen at gully
better shot, a front-foot drive to one pitched up, but right to cover
too full first off and Styris drives to Sidebottom's left at mid-off

good shout, ball pitching on about leg stump and went across, Flynn very late on the shot, ball hits him with the angle and to the naked eye it seemed ball would have hit about off stump, but umpire Nigel Llong doesn't think so
short of a length outside off stump and he leaves it be
full and wide, and crashed very hard out to deep extra cover
good ball, change of pace and it lands on a good length, holding its line after pitching and just skimming past Flynn'f forward defensive
and again! Nearly cuts him in half, this one on the stumps and seaming back in to get Flynn tucking up and playing inside the line .. how did that miss the edge?
tossed up outside off, spins in and Styris works it to midwicket
tossed up wider, he strides forward and nudges to point for one
flat on middle and off, good dip, Flynn defends solidly
spins down leg stump, worked straight to midwicket
teenie bit of air now, landing on off stump, driven to point
good ball, full and flat on middle and off, driven with an inside-edge
short of a length, he flicks it from outside off past midwicket
gets him going back and defending to Pietersen at point
shorter one, Styris gets tall and pushes one into the gap at cover
pitches on leg and goes across, Flynn turns it past midwicket for two
cracking shot, Flynn throwing the kitchen sink at the short and wide delivery and going right over point, out to where Cook dives on the rope but can't prevent four
short again, but cramping Flynn, who mistimes the flick back to Wright
flat on off stump, Styris comes forward and drives to mid-on
well done, from around the stumps, drifting into middle and leg and taking the thick inside-edge back onto Flynn's pads
slower through the air, pitching on middle, worked to midwicket
flat outside off stump, drawing a loose defensive to backward point
comes forward and drives hard to extra cover for one
flat on off stump, worked past midwicket, wants two but Broad is quick
gentle one on middle and off, on-driven to the fielder running in
shorter, he moves back and gently runs it to a sliding Bopara at point
good shot, aerial though it may have been, as Styris gets back and drives off the back foot into the gap between cover and point
short but not short enough to be pulled, as Flynn finds out with a mistimed cramped shot, crunching the ball into the ground in front of midwicket
drops the soft hands over this one, fuller, and does a tip-and-run
back of a length and Styris pushes off the back foot to cover
sashays down, collects on the full, and goes over mid-on, who's inside
short and flat, he works across the line past a diving midwicket

and another drop, this time Bopara letting one go at backward point, leaping up to try and catch a Styris slash in the air, its a sharp one but he only gets his right hand onto it, allowing a run as well
full and flat, he comes forward and squeezes a single
full on middle and off, flicked across the line for one more
short, spins back in and Flynn, backing away, cuts vert late
short of a length and he gets back to play it back to Wright
there's the 100, Flynn pulling a short ball behind square for one

slog this time, a real agricultural swat across the line as he steps aside, and very fortunate to escape with a genuine french cut down to fine leg, where some spiffing sliding from Shah saves one run
goes to drive a fuller one, too much bottom hand, mid-on runs in
good length that, and Flynn presents a full face to defend
gets some room and cuts off the front foot past cover, hustling hard
flat on off stump, gets forward and nudges past Bell at midwicket
speared into middle and leg from around the stumps, defended
some air this time, dipping and looping outside off stump, Flynn gets across and tries to sweep hard but misses out
flat on off stump and this time he defends, patiently

dropped again! A tough chance by Bell at cover, as Flynn advances and drives hard in the air, Bell dives to his right and sticks out a hand but cannot hang on ... he's taken some blinders before, so thats got to disappoint Bell ... England are having a poor day in the field .. .where's Pietersen and his cigar?
flat again, he gets back and works the ball away, fielder throws and misses
well bowled, angling across, dropped at his feet and scampers
good ball, shorter and moving away, he has a flirt and misses
fuller, middle and off, flicked anxiously past Pietersen at midwicket
pitches outside leg stump, he's late on the shot, half-appeal from Wright
shorter, going across, flicked across the line to deep midwicket
some room outside off and cut into the covers for a single
flat into leg stump, pushed gently to cover and sprints off
tossed up outside off, it spins in and Styris cant time his nudge
fuller and he shuffles across, driving uppishly to mid-on, who's deep
tossed up generously, Flynn waits and cuts, but Wright dives at gully
tossed up outside off and he goes sweeping, missing out
flatter now, and Flynn plays against the spin, flicking to midwicket
big appeal first ball as Flynn plays across the line, but it pitched outside leg
defended back to Bopara in his follow through
good line and Flynn flicks down the on side again, Bopara scuttles across to field
flicked in the air, evades midwicket and races across the outfield for a welcome boundary...brings up the fifty stand
along the ground past midwicket this time, not with the same force and it's hauled in
driven in the air through mid-off, down to the long-off fielder
hint of spin from outside off, tucked through the leg side
gone, superb bowling from Swann as he tosses this up on middle stump, Flynn drives and is beaten in the air...key breakthrough for England
stays round the wicket, hint of turn takes a thick outside edge down to short third man
drifts onto leg stump, takes the pad down to short fine-leg
tossed up very full, punted down to the ground to get Oram up and away
turned into the leg side...good over from Swann
opens the face and runs down to third man

good line on off stump, angled down fine of backward point to third man...Sidebottom has had the wood over Oram for much of the last five months these two sides have been playing (it feels like longer)
beaten outside off as Styris prods at this without much footwork...went with the slope
down the leg side, gets away with the wide as umpire Llong thinks it flicked the pad
defended down to backward point with an open face
straighter from Sidebottom, tucked towards square leg and he keeps the strike
worked off the body down to long leg
round the wicket, on off stump, defended square on the off side
short outside off, Oram cuts this hard square past point and it races away, beating third man to the boundary...there were shouts of 'catch' but he found the gap
pushed into the gap at cover this time, good batting
short and wide, slammed square through the off side straight at the sweeper
defended down to mid-off
hint of width, Styris frees his arms through the covers
good bouncer, over middle and off, requires a late duck and weave from Oram
short, wide and hammered, but Sidebottom gets away with a loose ball because there's a cover sweeper in the deep
short and pulled away through square leg this time, picks out deep square-leg
defends off the back foot, gets a thick inside half of the bat through square and it's placed in the gap for two...the bowler not happy
pushed through the covers out to the sweeper
tries to guide this to third man, doesn't make contact
tight line on middle, defended into the off side and eventually Oram agrees to the single...takes a while to get moving
flicked through midwicket, speed gun said 92mph for that one...not quite sure
upper-cut down to third man, goes one bounce to Sidebottom...Oram wasn't trying to keep that down
went wide on the crease, short ball angled into Styris' body, opens the face down to third man
banged in, flies high and wide of Oram past off stump...he'll have to bowl that one again
tucked off the pads, just to the left of mid-on
pushed comfortably up to long-off, Oram now happy to get onto the front foot
full and wide, gives Styris the chance to free his arms through point...well timed and it races away to beat the cover sweeper
driven on the up through the covers, this time straight at the sweeper
lucky to get away with that, gave Oram width but he just slapped it into the ground and the ball bobbled to cover
there he goes, Oram opens up and picks this one from off stump high over wide long-on, it comfortably goes all the way...danger signs for England
low full toss, nudged down to long-off, good over for New Zealand and Oram
round the wicket, tucked off leg stump in front of square
worked from off stump out to deep square-leg
goes for the reverse sweep, doesn't really get it right, takes the pad down to short third man
driven on the up past extra cover, long-off keeps them to a single
almost gets a leading edge to cover as he tries to turn this square
flicked along the ground straight at midwicket...good comeback from Swann
cut from off stump to short third man
dragged down short, but just flicked out to deep square-leg...this gentle off spin will be very tempting for Oram
driven firmly back to Shah in his follow through
flicked to short midwicket, can't find the gap
punched down to long off
full on off stump, driven out to deep cover, tidy start for Shah
turn from outside off, dropped into the off side, some confusion over wanting a single...they decide against it
nicely bowled, beats Styris on the outside edge as he drives

good work from Ambrose, Styris beaten again on the outside and drags his back foot a touch...this is mighty close and the third umpire will need a good look at this, but Styris gets the benefit of the doubt
good stuff from Swann, thumped back down the pitch
worked from off stump out to deep square-leg
worked out to midwicket, sharp single to end the over
wide, short and slammed late through the covers
back and rather cramped poke up to mid-off
driven on the walk to mid-on
swept but not fine enough, deep backward square leg fields
turned off the pads to deep midwicket, a walked single
fired in, driven into the on side past a tumbling Shah and another gentle amble through for the single
skips down the track, opens the face and hits over the infield, dropping short of deep cover despite some excitement from the England players
off the angled face, Cook in quickly at backward point
pretty horrible attempt at a reverse sweep but without changing his hands. he misses and the balls plops off the pads into the off side
kept down to the single into the conventional leg side
turned behind square on the leg side
pushed into space on the leg side, another single but not a productive over for New Zealand
firm pushed-drive to longish-on
another half volley, in the slot, thumped over long-on. It didn't get that high but it was well over the fielder
pushed through the covers
Shah fires one in but Oram swings and thumps that into the top tier of the Edrich Stand ...massive
clipped to backward point ... a dot ball no less
flicked off the pads to deep midwicket, they push for the second and it's easy as Broad's throw is almost exactly between the sets of stumps
firm off driven well stopped by the captain at short extra cover
cramped and back to the bowler
spooned into the on side, a nothing shot but he gets away with it
looks for the easy single  but there are no gaps on the on side
an ironic cheer as he does push it between fielders on the leg side and strolls for the single
Oram gives himself room and looks to clear long-off, but he underclubs and Broad takes a straightforward catch seven or eight yards in front of the pavilion
wristy whip off middle and leg to deep square leg
good line and length, he can do no more than block
into the off side where the cordon has been strengthened for Elliott ... the backroom boys have spotted something
another attempt to dab the ball behind square on the off, but there are two men there for that very shot
short and wide, slammed hard enough to get through point, Sidebottom fields in the deep but not well and his speed and dreadful throw allows the second
mistimes a pull, off body rather than than bat, it plops behind square and Ambrose can't prevent the single
that would have been a leg-side wide but Elliott had moved so far to leg that it passed between him and the stumps and he played a wild heave
into the on side off his body, more defensive than intentional but he gets off the strike which is what New Zealand need
Styris's turn to have a complete heave, but head up and he misses, the ball passing a couple of feet over middle stump
too short, Styris hooks off the bottom of the bat, no idea where it was going but it clears the rope at fine leg
super drive down the ground, high and to the right of the pavilion, but it plugs a few feet short of the wooden railings and so no boundary
reaches and steers a wide delivery to the right of a diving point, he stops it but can't prevent the run
half volley driven from wide of the crease to extra cover
another half volley, in the slot, thumped over long-on. It didn't get that high but it was well over the fielder
pushed through the covers
cut hard to third man, a good diving stop from Bopara who flicks the ball back on the boundary edge and fires in a good return. Sidebottom applauds
a swing and a miss
into the off side, a low key end to a productive over
slower ball leaves Styris looking a complete novice as he drives at air
full toss leaves Anderson looking like a novice, flicked dismissively one bounce past wide midwicket
wide, driven almost on the full through the covers
wide and slower, Elliott had committed to giving himself room and has to really reach to even get a bottom edge on the ball which then dribbles through to the keeper
full toss hit hard to deep cover
wide long hop, got everything that it asked for, slammed high over the point boundary into the mass of people clutching the sponsor's boundary cards
good fielding by Bopara in the deep prevents the second, a rifled throw was well
full and wide, all Styris can do is squeeze it through the covers
angled in at his feet, cramped, and all he can do is dig it out and take the single
half volley smashed to long-on, they risk the second at this stage of the innings and get it with ease
swung from half-volley length on off stump through midwicket
take that! Heaved into the top tier of the Grandstand, and for those of you who know Lord's, you will know that's high. Poor bowling, it was in the groove but he got hold of it and some ...
short and pulled past midwicket and Bopara in the deep can't cut it off.
steered down to third man
wide outside off, Styris swings and misses
yorker-length outside off, driven to deep cover
slower ball driven off middle-and-off to deep cover
yorker length outside off, squeezed too fine for third man to have any chance. That was 96 off the last ten ....

inn2.comm: swing through the air, as Bell walks down the crease first ball, Mills knew he was coming and fired it on the legs and Bell nervously poked that to cover
but thats timed sumptously off the legs, driven on the up past mid-on
back of a length and he gets in line, defending
that one's pushed towards the infield
urm ... wrong line, on the pads and turned effortlessly past midwicket
thats the spot, lands on a good length and shaves past the bat
gentle ball, just angled across Cook, who holds back the bat
poor start, this one pitching well down Cook's pads for a wide
some shape, but not much, as the ball lands outside off and Cook leaves
holds back the length a tad and Cook hurries to defend to point
firm push off the front foot, confident to go after the fuller one, to cover
back in his crease, pushing the shorter one to the man at point
edged and it doesn't carry to Styris at second slip, Cook feeling for that
full on off stump, Bell again looks to get across, has to adjust and drive to cover, where Vettori slides and fields
short of a length and angling in and he nudges one to square leg
goes flashing a wide one with no footwork and doesn't connect, McCullum collects and has a shout of some sort, prompting Mills to cherp in
firm shot, Cook getting off the mark in his first match since back in February, putting away the poor wide ball from Mills with an authoritative slap past cover
short of a length on the stumps and he pushes it to the fielder
back and across, tapping this good-length ball back to Mills
shuffles across, as he likes too, and is late on the attempted flick, ball strikes him  above the knee roll, they all appeal but Bell has come a long way forward
beaten, as Gillespie holds the back the length and gets this one to straighten
good ball, jagging back in a bit and forcing Bell to defend to point
again he walks down and Gillespie adjusts the length, so Bell defends
gets back and punches the width but cannot beat the man at cover
another shout for leg-before, as Bell again shuffles across, but once more he's got a long way forward and that one was sliding down, in fact it brushed his pads and runs away to fine leg
pushes uppishly off the front foot, reaching out, to Vettori at mid-off
dropped short and Cook pulls in a flash, in front of midwicket, Elliott sets off but the ball wins that little battle
slower ball, full and getting Cook forward and defending
another full ball and again Cook strides forward and defends
edgy shot there, as Cook flirts away from the body and steers the wide one to backward point, Oram, who is fooled by the bounce and allows one
short of a length on off stump, Bell gets across and defends
drives a full one, inside-edges to midwicket, sets off, and Flynn dives
oversteps, Bell taps to midwicket with a firm 'NO' and we've a free hit
full outside off, nearly a yorker, Bell backs away and swings, only inside-edging into the gap at short fine leg and thats a four off the freebie
good length on off, defended with soft hands and he scampers one to leg
pushed across his stumps and he leaves it be
short of a length, tucks him up and he nudges to midwicket
fuller ball, he gets forward and defends to midwicket again
good-length ball on off stump, patted back towards Mills
back of a length, this time he gently pushes the ball to cover and runs
fuller ball on off stump, tucked away to midwicket for one
walks across his stumps, working the ball from off to midwicket
too straight, but thats more a good shuffling shot, out to deep square leg
short ball on the stumps, he pulls well past midwicket
good length ball on the stumps, driven to the man inside
short of a length, he gets back and inside-edges to midwicket
short of a length and he gets back and punching to cover
nips back in, rapping him on the pad but outside leg stump
gets across, working the ball across from off stump to midwicket
well bowled, this one off a shorter length and zipping away to beat the bat
too short and he pulls from outside off stump to midwicket
shuffles across and plays the straighter one superbly to fine leg
holds back the length outside off and now Bell taps to point
now he pokes at one lifting outside off, feet not moving, and misses
short of a length and thats slapped off the back foot to gully
well played, Bell, getting onto the toes and pushing the short ball through cover, on the up and all timing and placement, pleasing to see
well bowled, pitching and straightening to beat the bat
pushes down the wrong line and gets beaten
short of a length and he defends that one to midwicket
this one's fuller and he drives into the covers, where Vettori dives
good length ball on off, Bell gets across and works it to midwicket
short of a length, angling in, Bell shuffles and drops it into the gap at leg
good length to start off, and Cook gets well forward to defend
half-appeal as that one pitches outside the stumps and comes back in to catchi him very high on the flap,  ball rolls towards point
confident shout, but that one pitches marginally outside leg stump before Cook shuffled across and tried the flick, not getting bat on it
down he walks, getting across to nudge from off stump to square leg
good shot to raise England's fifty, Cook shuffling across and flicking a ball from middle stump, while airborn, and picks the yawning gap behind square
fuller length outside off and this time Cook defends coming forward
not this time, sorry! Bell for the umpteenth time shuffles across his stumps and tries to flick one that doesn't go on as he expected, ball pitches and straightens and thats pretty plumb
welcome, welcome ... Gillespie drops in a snorter that gets generous purchase off the deck, Pietersen hops up and gets bat out of the way just in time
short of a length and he gets in line, watchfully defending down
well done, Gillespie! This one straightens and beats his bat again, squaring up Pietersen who pushes forward and misses the line of the ball
gets across and forward, defending back to Gillespie
back of a length, Pietersen behind it defending to point, compactly
touch too short, Cook shuffles, picking from outside off to deep midwicket

back of a length and he's on his toes, driving back past an urgent Pietersen, already off the blocks in a flash and making sure's running in the thrower's aim from mid-off, so he gets down the other end with ease, well run
gets right outside the stumps, exposing middle and leg, Oram drops it short, Pietersen defends, bowler collects and throws it back towards the stumps
well played, shuffling across and driving towards midwicket, running hard, two men converge near deep mid-on but the batsmen have come back for the second
fuller and wider, Pietersen comes onto the front foot and leaves
back of a length and he's right on top of it, defending to cover
quality shot, flicked from middle and off past midwicket for two
gone now! Southee doesn't take long to strike, pitching fuller and angling it away and Cook hops up to defend, undone by the lack of bounce and the thinnest of edges is snapped
slower ball first up and Bopara defends solidly off the front foot
defends a straighter one and inside-edges to midwicket
uses his feet and comes well forward, steering a full one to point
straighter one, Bopara gets across and drives it back to Southee
full and coming in, defended with an inside-edge to square leg
comes onto the front foot and drives the ball towards point
gest across his stumps and defends with a full face of the bat
again, gets across and drives the ball towards the fielder
well clipped, taking the full ball from middle and off past midwicket
walks down the track, Oram holds back the length, defended to cover
flicked down in front of midwicket
flashes outside off stump, no footwork, but gets away with it
hint of movement into Bopara, defended off the front foot into the leg side
outside off stump, takes half a stride forward and drives to mid-on without much timing
forced off the back foot, played down by his feet...impressive stuff from Southee
dragged down short wide, Bopara goes after it but doesn't make contact...poor shot, poor ball
lovely shot, overpitched on middle stump, Bopara eases it through a wide mid-on...that will release the pressure for a moment
defended from outside off into the leg side...the usual extravagant movement from Pietersen
goes right across his crease and then leaves alone as Oram sticks to his testing line and length
pulls this way from outside off stump, didn't middle it, more bottom edge really and goes to deep square-leg
thick outside edge from Bopara, falls short of gully, and Oram proving a handful
this time there's a loose ball from Oram, short and wide, Bopara dispatches it through point
back on line, outside off stump and Bopara defends down to mid-off
takes the pad behind square on the leg side as Pietersen doesn't make contact
fuller on off stump, driven up to mid-on
nearly squeezes through as Bopara inside edges a drive into his pads
that's a top shot, taken from off stump and on-drive down past the stumps...out of the textbook
edgy this time from Bopara as he plays away from his body and the ball flies into the leg side
outside off and left alone
outside off, Bopara takes a big stride and defends with his head right over the ball
nicely bowled, hint of shape outside off and Bopara is beaten
all in defence as Oram remains on his tight off-stump line
angled into the off side, finds space between point and cover
steps outside off stump, finishes by defending into the leg side...he hasn't got going yet
touch of extra bounce, Pietersen has to take his bottom hand off the bat as he defends to midwicket
pushed firmly out to backward point
top shot from Bopara, dragged down short and it sat up nicely, he rolled his wrists and set it rocketing to the deep square-leg boundary
fuller and on the pads, flicked along the deck but Mills gets round this time and keeps it to a single
whipped firmly off middle stump, but he can't find the gap and picks out midwicket

gone! what a breakthrough and that is a huge moment in this match...given a hint of width from Southee but he can't get on top of it, slicing in the air to backward point where Oram takes a good catch
defences in his own unique style into the leg side
a wild drive from Bopara, his eyes lit up at the width, and it's so wide that umpire Davis calls it
driven up to mid-off...this is a huge partnership now for England
defended to cover, Oram proving difficult to get away
defended on off stump, cover in action again
tries to run this one fine, but gets it too square and picks out backward point
walks across his crease and exploits a huge gap in the leg side
outside off, left alone, good carry through to McCullum who takes around his shoulders
flicked off leg stump through the leg side
turned off the stumps into midwicket, Shah wants to push for two but they decide against it
rides it nicely round the corner, again calls are for two but it's not on as Mills has a decent arm
defended back down the pitch, Southee fields in his follow through
defended out to extra cover
lucky for Shah, goes for the pull and gets a bottom edge past the stumps...was close to the end for Shah
punched up to long-off
comes forward, defends into the leg side
comes down the pitch, doesn't quite get to the pitch so defends
waits for this outside off, plays it late square on the off side
goes for an ambitious sweep from outside off, misses and there's an appeal from New Zealand but he didn't hit it
nicely bowled on off stump, defended into the covers...excellent start from Vettori
put away in impressive style, enough width for Bopara to free his hands at the ball and sent it through the covers
back on a good line and length, defended solidly down the track
touch short, Bopara stands tall in the crease and defends to the leg side
opens the face, guided away through point
good yorker from Southee, on middle and leg, dug out to midwicket
driven firmly down to mid-off, good comeback from Southee after that first ball
a punchy drive down to long off to bring up England's 100
rocks back, defends into the leg side
eased down to long on, these two just trying to establish a platform like Oram and Styris did

gone! but they won't be doing it any longer, a brilliant piece of bowling by Vettori as he beats Bopara with an arm ball that slides on and crashes into the stumps...Bopara was trying to glide that away but was completely done in the flight
driven out to cover
takes the inside edge into the leg side...a fine over from Vettori
on middle, defended back down the pitch
whipped into the leg side with a flourish of the wrists
outside off, flicked down to third man
cut away into the off side, goes one bounce to backward point
tight line on off stump, defended back to Styris
pushed out to midwicket, just a single from the over and New Zealand firmly in control at the moment
nice flight on off stump, played softly into the off side
comes down the pitch and sends this one bounce to long off
defended to the off side
goes for a big drive, gets an inside edge into his boot
looped up on middle and leg, all defence from Wright
excellent stuff from Vettori, teasing on off stump, Wright just blocks him out
driven down to long on, Wright again has five balls to face
heaved away through the leg side off one knee, not convincing and he tried to launch that
defended from middle and off back down the pitch, Styris doing a great job here
driven firmly and straight at mid-off...Vettori confident enough to have plenty of fielders inside the circle
blocked from middle stump down the on side
seams into Shah, whipped off the pads down to long leg and he comes back for a couple...first time there's been more than a single for a while
plays this very late, cuts from just outside off stump to backward point
lovely bowling from Vettori, tempting Wright with flight on off stump, cut away again
onto the front foot, dropped into the covers, Wright races off for a single but is sent back...there was probably a single on offer
this time places it between cover and point, both batsmen agree on the run
defended from off stump into the covers
tucked into the leg side, keeps the strike but the asking rate continues to climb
dropped tough chance at mid-off as Shah goes in the air, Vettori couldn't quite stretch fair enough to his left
huge appeal, that's close as Wright is rapped on the pads in front of off stump...maybe just outside the line, gee that was very close and Wright was lucky there
chopped away to backward point
defended back to Styris...pressure growing on England, require rate over seven and a half now
driven down to long on
nips back into Wright, takes the pad down to third man...a few scares in that over for England
full and flat on middle and off, uses his feet and drives to mid-off
comes down again and hits it wider this time
spun up very wide, Wright reaches out and slaps into the covers
what a lovely timed shot, Vettori straying gently onto Shah's leg stump and he gets back, flicking into the gap at square leg and the sweeper can't get there
fuller and flatter, as excected, and Shah on-drives a single
tossed up on a good length and Wright plays it back
gets across and tries to work this this to midwicket, but can't
too straight and he flicks from middle stump past square leg, sprinting
outside off and now Shah nudges softly into the covers, Oram chases
down the pads, smart stumping attempt from McCullum, but wide
well dabbed, very late, using the width to steer to short third man
short of a length but down the pads and Shah wrists it to square leg
nips in, Wright nudges towards square leg and runs hard
bowled em with a quicker ball! Vettori is too much for the likes of Wright, backing away, trying to cut the arm ball, and he's in no spot to tackle that and the stumps are splayed
down leg, looping, and he runs it off the pads to midwicket
hint of turn, spinning away, Ambrose defends towards point
slower, much flatter, and he comes forward to defend
ooo ... didn't really pick that one, pushing at it with a stride in, the ball turns and takes a bit of an edge and Marshall fields at backward point
better shot, cutting the short one into the covers for one
nips back in and beats a nervous Ambrose, cut in half, losing a hand
pushes away from the body, off the front foot, and edges wide of gully
beaten here, also pushing away from the body as the ball skims away
bang, thats four, Shah swivels off the front foot and hits one off the middle, pulling a short one over mid-on
stands his ground and cuts a wide one down into the ground past gully
change of pace, closer to the stumps, defended, calling 'no, no ...'
full and flat, sliding down, Ambrose pushes with a thick inside-edge
looped up down leg, run off the pads to midwicket
pushed through flatter and he comes forward to defend
quicker, wider, and Ambrose cannot control himself from reaching out and slapping that one tamely to Marshall, the substitute, at backward point
quick and flat outside off, he strides well forward and pads it
whats wrong with that? Bold shot from Swann, trying to sweep from middle stumps, beaten, ball spins in and Vettori cannot believe thats not out! Well bowled, skip!
back of a length and he drives that towards cover
leading-edge as Shah tries to work it from off stump, running wide of gully
nips in off a length and Swann runs it to backward point
lifter now, fairly kicking up from a length outside off stump, Swann sways
goes poking outside off this time, connecting with nuttin but air
thinks about playing but pulls back at the nth second as it shapes past
gets forward, then back, and slaps this hard past cover, Southee out at sweeper slides and does well to save runs
sweeps in the air, but the ball drops just in front of Gillespie in the deep, then he fumbles and allows the extra run
quicker one, he gets back and defends
nearly a collision! Shah pokes this towards point and sets off, Shah runs straight and then tries to get out of the ball's way and nearly runs into Vettori ... wouldn't that have sparked debates?
full and flat, he backs away and drives towards cover
wider one, Shah reaches out and slaps this away for one
slow ball first up, Shah comes out and drives to Vettori at mid-off
lands on a length, Swann comes forward and drives into the covers
not a bad shout, Shah stepping across and trying to swat this one to fine leg, cannot get bat on it, Mills appeals but that was missing leg stump
slower ball, nearly a yorker, well jammed out to extra cover for one
oh now thats sloppy! Swann backs away and drills this one over the covers, it bounces once in front of Flynn who cups his hands one way and allows the ball to go the other
well played, walking across his stumps and flicking past square leg
slower ball drifting into leg stump, Shah makes room and taps to point
wrong line, too much width, Swann waits and waits and cuts past cover
too full, well down leg stump, beats Swann and McCullum, batsmen run one, a fumble and poor throw from square leg allows the second
looped in down leg stump and Swann can't time his drive
quicker and flatter on middle and off and he defends
hint of drift, spins down leg, defended again
down leg stump, brushes his pads and they scamper a run

well held, McCullum! Swann walks across his stumps to try and paddle-pull the short one angling down leg, he doesn't get more than a tickle on it and McCullum flings himself to his left and holds a good catch
short of a length and he drives it straight to point
fuller now and he goes for an airy drive, missing completely
and again, feet not moving, head not still, and he's beaten on the drive
better shot, driving a wide half-volley straight to cover
another loose waft outside off, another miss ... "that would be out in baseball!" chirps someone in these necks of the woods
played square on the off side
nudged through midwicket
over the wicket, angling into leg stump, swept to short fine-leg
nice flight, Shah can only push it back down the pitch
slotted square out to deep cover
ends with a dot as Broad jabs it back down the pitch...another outstanding spell from the New Zealand captain
full on off stump, dug out into the off side
low full toss, swung high over midwicket and Mark Gillespie makes a bit of a mess of trying to prevent the boundary
good response, full outside off dug out past Mills down to long on...Mills feels he should have fielded that
tries to swing this through the leg side, gets a bottom edge into his legs
driven on the up straight out to cover

carved just over backward point, oh dear that's a shoddy piece of work by Southee at third man as he lets it slip through his rather lame efforts to stop it...won't cost New Zealand, but they have high standards
low full toss outside off, driven to cover inside the circle
thumped down to long off and some sharp running from Broad completes two
another full toss, heaved down to long on and takes him to fifty off 63 balls...he's been the best England batsman of this series, although hasn't always had much competition
wide outside off, Broad gives himself room but doesn't make contact as it flies out of the footmarks and eludes McCullum
cheeky from Shah, goes down on one knee and sweeps over short fine-leg...some late defiance
full and dug out towards deep cover
very full outside off, driven with force one bounce out to deep cover
the low full toss gets a wicket, Broad heaves it down deep square-leg throat as he tries to clear the rope...Daniel Flynn holds the catch above his head
goes slightly inside out through extra cover, long-off scampers around to prevent the boundary
another full toss, maybe it's a tactic, sliced through cover
dropped into the off side, Sidebottom is away
driven out to the cover sweeper, Shah keeps the strike
wide outside off, helped through the off side but this is just playing out time
gives himself room and carves square through point, beats third man into the fence
pushed out to cover
dragged down short and wide, that'll be a wide...it is, I can pick these things
pushed into the covers
carved through the off side
strains too much and sends this very wide outside off
extraordinary shot from Shah, digs out almost a yorker-length ball with strong wrists and jabs it away over cover...it races away
round the wicket, driven down to long off
jabbed through extra cover, nicely timed and placed
low, straight full toss, whipped into midwicket but can't beat the sub, James Marshall
flashes and misses outside off
big full toss, bunted down the ground to long off
yorker outside leg stump, Shah gave himself room and blocked it out to cover to keep the strike
and he strikes, swung high down the ground by Shah and picks out James Marshall at long off...New Zealand now that's the match well and truly sown up, the celebrations can begin
full on the stumps, dug out square on the off side
angled down to third man
takes the pad down to third man
gives himself room and misses as the ball flies over middle stump...Southee has been impressive this series
goes down the leg side, Anderson misses his flick
backs away, gives himself room and misses another slash
carved down to long off
driven square through the off side
dropped backward point didn't see that as a thick outside edge flies his way...went straight through his hands
low full toss outside off, misses the drive
and that's that, sliced away to backward point, Oram takes the catch and Gillespie ends the match...New  Zealand all the way and huge smiles on all their faces
